Uh, I haven't blessed them yet.

12:58.559 --> 13:01.768
Well, in that case,
can I get a swig of wine?

13:01.835 --> 13:05.071
There'll be plenty of time
for that after you're married.

13:05.138 --> 13:07.908
‐ I'll see you at the altar.
‐ Alright.

13:07.974 --> 13:08.942
[sighs]

13:09.009 --> 13:10.844
You're not nervous,
Overton, are you, man?

13:10.911 --> 13:13.146
‐ Give me that.
‐ Yeah, I'm nervous, man.

13:13.213 --> 13:14.681
My parents haven't showed up.

13:14.748 --> 13:18.084
I‐I just passed out, and
I still ain't seen that ring.

13:18.151 --> 13:20.987
Here, look. Satisfied?

13:21.054 --> 13:24.525
Man, I hope I'm not this
jittery the day of my wedding.

13:24.591 --> 13:27.393
Yeah, that's 'cause you'd be
too busy arguin' with Max

13:27.460 --> 13:29.530
over who's gonna wear the tux.

13:31.264 --> 13:32.999
‐ Max?
‐ Yeah.

13:33.066 --> 13:35.669
I mean, tragic as it is, shorty

13:35.736 --> 13:37.103
she's your destiny.

13:39.239 --> 13:41.141
What have we here?

13:41.207 --> 13:43.844
A brick house
in the house of the Lord.

13:46.146 --> 13:47.948
Hey, Russell.

13:48.014 --> 13:50.751
Have I ever thanked you for that
lunch we had the other day?

13:50.817 --> 13:52.919
That was six months ago.

13:52.986 --> 13:55.255
And I gave you the chance
to thank me properly

13:55.321 --> 13:57.123
but you kept your clothes on.

14:00.360 --> 14:03.303
Baby, don't run off like that.
I missed you crazy.

14:08.675 --> 14:09.910
Regine, Tanya.

14:09.976 --> 14:11.111
Tanya, Regine.

14:11.177 --> 14:12.312
Charmed.

14:13.547 --> 14:15.148
[chuckles]
Ah, come on, Russell.

14:15.215 --> 14:17.551
Let's see how our names look
together in the guest book.

14:22.923 --> 14:25.258
A man can't wait
forever, Regine.

14:29.295 --> 14:30.631
(Max)
'Hey, girl.'

14:30.697 --> 14:33.099
Aren't you the sorriest‐looking
fireplug on the street, girl?

14:33.166 --> 14:35.401
You look tore up.
What's wrong with you?

14:35.468 --> 14:36.703
Oh, you're pathetic,
you know that.

14:36.770 --> 14:38.371
Phony concern from somebody

14:38.438 --> 14:40.974
who only cries when
we run out of Miracle Whip.

14:42.876 --> 14:44.811
I care.

14:44.878 --> 14:46.847
And to prove it,
here's something

14:46.913 --> 14:48.849
that's sure to cheer you up.

14:50.517 --> 14:54.220
Kyle and I have been
seeing each other for months.

14:58.124 --> 15:00.193
But it's over now

15:00.260 --> 15:03.403
and you missed every
freaky‐sneaky detail.

15:05.138 --> 15:08.809
Oh. And everybody knew, but you.

15:13.346 --> 15:15.281
Alright, ladies, one minute.

15:18.752 --> 15:19.686
[door slams]

15:21.221 --> 15:24.290
‐ Oh, hi, Khadijah.
‐ Hey.

15:24.357 --> 15:26.492
Uh, Max, can I talk
to you for a minute?

15:26.560 --> 15:28.328
Alright..

15:29.563 --> 15:31.431
Uh..

15:31.497 --> 15:33.634
Look, after all
we've been through

15:33.700 --> 15:36.803
it doesn't seem right
to end on such a sour note.

15:36.870 --> 15:39.673
So I just wanted
to tell you that, uh

15:39.740 --> 15:41.708
I really have enjoyed
knowing you.

15:41.775 --> 15:44.678
Despite our numerous
psychotic episodes.

15:46.379 --> 15:49.650
Knowing you hasn't been
entirely stomach‐turning.

15:49.716 --> 15:51.852
[chuckles]

15:51.918 --> 15:55.889
Well, anyway, um, I have decided
to take that job in London.

15:55.956 --> 15:58.258
‐ Onward and upward.
‐ Yeah.

15:58.324 --> 16:00.827
So, um, if you ever feel like

16:00.894 --> 16:03.136
legally driving
on the wrong side of the road

16:03.203 --> 16:04.705
give me a call.

16:06.607 --> 16:07.874
I love you.

16:12.713 --> 16:14.515
Wh‐what?

16:14.581 --> 16:15.782
Huh?

16:15.849 --> 16:17.017
Come on, you guys!
Come on.

16:17.083 --> 16:19.485
We got 30 seconds. Let's go.

16:30.531 --> 16:33.433
Hey, try and walk like a lady.

16:34.568 --> 16:35.502
Go.

16:38.672 --> 16:40.741
[whispering]
Max, stop it!

16:40.807 --> 16:43.510
Excuse me. I just can't
stop staring at you.

16:43.577 --> 16:46.112
Would you like
to have dinner sometime?

16:46.179 --> 16:47.447
Desmond Howard?

16:47.514 --> 16:49.983
Yep, I'm Overton's cousin,
Smoke Eye's son.

16:51.217 --> 16:54.320
Oh. Oh, save me a dance
at the reception.

16:57.157 --> 16:59.459
Oh, thank you.

16:59.526 --> 17:01.668
You're good
and you're fast.

17:05.105 --> 17:06.507
Whoo. Okay.

17:07.941 --> 17:09.976
Alright, boo,
I'm goin' in.

17:10.042 --> 17:12.512
Alright, you warm up
the crowd for me, okay?

17:12.579 --> 17:15.048
Okay. Okay.
Y'all watch my back.

17:15.115 --> 17:16.382
Keep me company.

17:16.449 --> 17:18.318
[instrumental music]

17:18.384 --> 17:21.221
(Synclaire)
'Okay.'

17:21.287 --> 17:23.289
Now, you make sure
you walk real slow, okay?

17:23.356 --> 17:25.592
I know, you want
to savor the moment.

17:25.659 --> 17:26.693
That, and I'm afraid
of slippin'

17:26.760 --> 17:28.493
on all those rose petals
out there.

17:28.561 --> 17:30.330
[laughing]
I love you.

17:30.396 --> 17:32.188
Oh, I love you, too, daddy.

17:32.188 --> 17:33.192
Come on.

17:39.039 --> 17:41.975
<i>["Wedding March" plays]</i>

17:48.815 --> 17:50.416
This is so beautiful.

17:50.483 --> 17:52.553
[sobbing]
Yes, it is.

17:53.687 --> 17:55.589
Now, I gotta get Regine hitched

17:55.656 --> 17:58.058
so she can get
some beans in that oven.

17:58.124 --> 17:59.960
Okay.

18:00.026 --> 18:01.568
Dearly beloved

18:01.635 --> 18:04.437
this is indeed a glorious day.

18:04.505 --> 18:05.572
Come on, shake a leg, Otis.

18:05.639 --> 18:07.073
Our pumpkin's about
to tie the knot.

18:07.140 --> 18:08.441
Odelle, I told you.

18:08.509 --> 18:11.211
Travel by bus is
cost‐effective and timely.

18:11.277 --> 18:14.047
Fine. You take
the bus back. I'm flying.

18:14.114 --> 18:17.450
Two of God's children,
Overton and Synclaire

18:17.518 --> 18:19.953
'are going to be
joined as one.'

18:24.024 --> 18:26.359
And now the maid of honor
and best man

18:26.426 --> 18:28.695
will pay tribute
to our blessed couple

18:28.762 --> 18:31.665
with a song written
by Brother Kyle.

18:31.732 --> 18:34.500
[instrumental music]

